AB  - Bank loan commitments backing commercial paper issues (other than credit guarantees) insure against systematic liquidity risk by providing an alternative to rolling over maturing paper. The form of these commitment contracts, the fact that they are issued only by banks, and the determinants of variation across issuers in the extent of commitment backing are consistent with their role as liquidity insurance and not with a recently espoused view that commitments signal firm quality.
